rows.label: qst200311_msg0002
rows.name:
I did bump into it by the main gate.
Literally? No, not literally.

rows.label: qst200311_msg0003
rows.name:
Ah, it was fine though. It didn't
do anythin', just sorta ran off.

rows.label: qst200311_msg0008
rows.name:
If you could find its
tracks, you could probably
follow 'em easy enough.

rows.label: qst200311_msg0004
rows.name: Mind you, Gogols are timid creatures.

rows.label: qst200311_msg0006
rows.name:
I think it's just confused after
Luxuria's isolation ended and people
started digging for salt everywhere...

rows.label: qst200311_msg0007
rows.name:
That's probably why it wandered
into town all of a sudden.
